column1: # Sample Transaction Data for Batch Processing Testing
# Data includes both valid and invalid transactions for comprehensive testing
# Valid Transactions - Various transaction types and amounts
# High-value transactions for credit limit testing
# Different card numbers for cross-reference testing
# Invalid Transactions for Testing Error Handling
# Invalid card number (should fail card validation)
# Transaction with expired date (future test for expiration validation)
# Very high amount (should test credit limit)
# Negative purchase amount (invalid - purchases should be positive)
# Missing required fields tests (empty transaction type)
# Special characters in merchant name for data validation
# Different transaction sources for processing logic testing
# Different zip code formats for validation
# Batch boundary testing - transactions around processing cutoff times
# Decimal precision testing for amount field
